This is not any sort of advice, but I feel like a good fraud to do would be=
 to send letters to every 25-to-35-year-old in the US that say =E2=80=9Chi,=
 I am your new student loan servicer, student loan payments are coming back=
, your new payment amount is $437 per month, here=E2=80=99s where you send =
a check.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s what a lot of student-loan servicers are=
=C2=A0legitimately=C2=A0doing, and how could anyone tell that you were lyin=
