<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possible interpretation of this case is th=
at the SEC=E2=80=99s decision to block spot Bitcoin ETFs was unusually egre=
gious, and a court fixed that, and there are no broader implications for an=
ything. And that=E2=80=99s possible, because the spot Bitcoin ETF decision =
really was weird. But another possible interpretation is that the modern SE=
C has become more aggressive about regulating the crypto industry, and the =
broader financial industry, in a lot of different areas, while the crypto a=
nd financial industries have become more aggressive about fighting back and=
 the modern US courts have become more aggressive about second-guessing the=
 SEC. The SEC has gotten used to its decisions being, for all practical pur=
poses, the law, and that might not be right anymore.</p>
