it wants to preserve Chief Executive Officer Jimmy Levin=E2=80=99s job. (Ri=
thm will leave Levin in charge of Sculptor; Weinstein probably wouldn=E2=80=
=99t.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And one tension is about how much Sculptor sho=
uld let Weinstein do to firm up his bid. On the one hand, $12.25 is more th=
an $11.15, and Sculptor=E2=80=99s board should want to maximize value for s=
hareholders, so it should engage with Weinstein. On the other hand, it ran =
an auction and picked the best bidder: It has some contractual=C2=A0obligat=
ions to preserve its deal with Rithm, and the losing bidders have some cont=
ractual obligations not to try to break up that deal. So Weinstein has=C2=
=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>put in a public proposal to buy Sculptor =E2=80=94=C2=
=A0that $12.25 proposal was delivered privately to the board, which then di=
sclosed it itself =E2=80=94=C2=A0because he=E2=80=99s not allowed to; his N=
DA doesn=E2=80=99t let him make public proposals. (Sculptor=E2=80=99s <a hr=
ef=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32547544.257429/aHR0cHM=
6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MDMyNTYvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIzMD=
QwNTk1L255MjAwMDk5Mzl4MV9wcmVtMTRhLmh0bSN0Qk0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf14b=
970a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" styl=
e=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width:=
 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-=
color: #ccc;"> merger proxy</a> discloses that it signed 25 NDAs in the auc=
tion process, of which 24 contained standstills and =E2=80=9Ctwenty-two of =
the standstill provisions contained =E2=80=98don=E2=80=99t ask/don=E2=80=99=
t waive=E2=80=99 provisions=E2=80=9D that prevent failed bidders from askin=
g the board to make another bid; Sculptor=E2=80=99s board waived those prov=
isions after hearing from Weinstein.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Meanwhile Sculptor=E2=80=99s estranged founder=
, Daniel Och, has been asking Sculptor to do more to waive those provisions=
 and let more people bid. He <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32547544.257429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9k=
YXRhLzE0MDMyNTYvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTIzMjIzMjExL2Q1NDkyMzZkZXg5OTMwLmh0bQ/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cB65c1463b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> sent the board another letter today</a>=
:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On August 22, 2023, we requested t=
hat you waive certain restrictions in the non-disclosure agreements with Bi=
dder J, Bidder H, and the Founders=E2=80=99 group (the =E2=80=9CNDAs=E2=80=
=9D), because we believed that preventing those bidders from publicly artic=
ulating their proposals and from speaking with us was contrary to the inter=
ests of shareholders. Specifically, we cannot understand how the Special Co=
mmittee could possibly conclude that it is in the best interests of shareho=
lders to deter us from communicating freely with such bidders to improve th=
eir bids, thereby reversing the prior massive diversion of value from share=
holders to management in order to achieve maximum value for all shareholder=
s.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyone buying Sculptor will have to deal with =
Och, who has a bunch of shares and some tax arrangements with Sculptor that=
 are worth a lot of money; one bidder in the initial auction seems to have =
dropped out because it couldn=E2=80=99t come to terms with Och. Letting pot=
ential bidders negotiate with Och would probably allow them to make their b=
ids, if not better, at least more certain. But when they signed up for the =
original auction they agreed not to talk to anyone else, because Sculptor=
=E2=80=99s board wanted to be in control of the sale process. But it is inc=
reasingly losing control.</p>
