<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not any sort of advice, but I feel lik=
e a good fraud to do would be to send letters to every 25-to-35-year-old in=
 the US that say =E2=80=9Chi, I am your new student loan servicer, student =
loan payments are coming back, your new payment amount is $437 per month, h=
ere=E2=80=99s where you send a check.=E2=80=9D That=E2=80=99s what a lot of=
 student-loan servicers are=C2=A0<em>legitimately=C2=A0</em>doing, and how =
could anyone tell that you were lying? The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/32547544.257429/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9wZXJzb2=
